  # 01 - Bruno Basics
  
  👋 Welcome to **Day 1** of the Bruno Starter Guide!
  
  In this challenge, you will:
  
  - ✅ Create a new request
  - ✅ Use different HTTP methods
  - ✅ Execute request
  
  ### Challenge Overview
  
  You'll learn the basics of Bruno — creating and executing your first request.
  
  ### 📌 Prerequisites
  
  - Bruno is installed and running
  - You know basic API terminology (like GET/POST)
  
  ### 📚 Instructions
  
  #### 🌐 Step 1: Create a Request
  
  1. Right click on `Basics` folder
  2. Select **New Request**.
  3. Name it `echo bruno`.
  4. Set method to **POST**.
  5. Enter URL: `https://echo.usebruno.com`
  6. Execute the request.
  
  Congrats on creating first request inside Bruno. 
  
  ### 📌 Summary  
  
  In this challenge, you have created your first request inside Bruno and executed it sucessfully.
}
